00:05:09.050 --> 00:05:13.590
and it was the Galileo
Spacecraft that went to Jupiter.

00:05:13.590 --> 00:05:16.640
So at that time, they
launched the spacecraft

00:05:16.640 --> 00:05:20.790
and it took six years before
it reached the planet.

00:05:20.790 --> 00:05:24.110
So there's a connection there
between the length of time

00:05:24.110 --> 00:05:28.060
and the days of old
exploration and space travel.

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:30.500
There's also another
anniversary of sorts today,

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:35.640
it was 20 years ago this month
